body:
The combination of Probes with output directory specification produces probes that are all in the default output directory. This is outside the FIRRTL spec. It is also inconsistent with how other things work. Consider the following:

```
FIRRTL version 3.3.0
circuit Foo: %[[
  {
    "class": "sifive.enterprise.firrtl.MarkDUTAnnotation",
    "target": "~Foo|Bar"
  },
  {
    "class": "sifive.enterprise.firrtl.TestBenchDirAnnotation",
    "dirname": "testbench"
  }
]]
  module Bar:
    output a: Probe<UInt<1>>

    node b = UInt<1>(0)
    define a = probe(b)

  module Foo:
    output a: Probe<UInt<1>>

    inst bar of Bar

    node b = UInt<1>(0)
    define a = probe(b)
```

When compiled using `firtool Foo.fir` this produces:

```verilog
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.57.1-81-g618c5e049
module Bar();
  wire _GEN = 1'h0;
endmodule


// ----- 8< ----- FILE "ref_Foo_Foo.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.57.1-81-g618c5e049
`define ref_Foo_Foo_a _GEN

// ----- 8< ----- FILE "ref_Foo_Bar.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.57.1-81-g618c5e049
`define ref_Foo_Bar_a _GEN

// ----- 8< ----- FILE "testbench/Foo.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.57.1-81-g618c5e049
// VCS coverage exclude_file
module Foo();
  wire _GEN = 1'h0;
  Bar bar ();
endmodule
```

It would be better if the `ref_Foo_Foo.sv` file was put in the `testbench/` directory. 

The example does not show this, but the same "correct" think should happen for anything related to GrandCentral. All the combinations that are tested in https://github.com/llvm/circt/blob/main/test/firtool/blackbox-directories.fir should work here.

h/t @drom for reporting this.
